      "message": "Won\u0027t land this as is, but I wanted to find out who used contains(x,y) for floats.\n\nIt has its own idea of inside... min \u003c\u003d value \u003c max for both X and Y\n\nIRect also has this, but (to me) this is more understandable, since we can think of the x,y as \"indexing\" a pixel, so this asymmetric predicate makes (more) sense.\n\n1. Do we really want this specific predicate at each of these call-sites?\n2. OK if I try to make this (or variants of it) private?\n",
